Imports look good, all names match `chat_db.py` exports. The implementation is complete.

## Final report

**File touched:** `server/chat_api.py` only.

**Actor resolution:** Replaced `_require_admin` with `_resolve_admin` (returns actor dict or `None`), `_require_admin` (rate-limits + raises 403, returns actor), `_require_super_admin` (raises 403 if not super_admin). Added `_protected_role` and `_guard_target` helpers. Added imports `get_admin, list_admins, add_admin, remove_admin, count_super_admins, log_admin_action, get_admin_actions, VALID_ADMIN_ROLES` from `chat_db`. `hash_email` and `get_user_by_token` were already imported — no change needed.

**Endpoints touched, actor tier, and action logged:**
- `admin_reports` (GET) — admin, no log (view-only)
- `admin_resolve_report` (PATCH) — admin, logs `resolve_report` (only on success, after the rowcount check)
- `admin_ban` (POST) — admin + `_guard_target`, logs `ban`
- `admin_unban` (POST) — super, logs `unban`
- `admin_delete_ban` (DELETE) — super, logs `delete_ban`
- `admin_get_settings` (GET) — admin, no log
- `admin_update_settings` (PATCH) — **super** (spec-mandated), logs `update_settings`
- `admin_stats`, `admin_users`, `admin_user_detail`, `admin_bans`, `admin_modlog`, `admin_rooms` (GET) — admin, actor threaded but unused (view-only)
- `admin_mute_user` (POST) — admin + `_guard_target`, logs `mute` or `ban` (escalation path)
- `admin_unmute_user` (POST) — admin, logs `unmute`
- `admin_strike_user` (POST) — admin + `_guard_target`, logs `result["action"]` (`strike`/`mute`/`ban`), skipped when `action == "none"`
- `admin_clear_warnings` (POST) — super, logs `clear_warnings`
- `admin_delete_user` (DELETE) — super + `_guard_target`, logs `delete_user`
- `admin_create_room` (POST) — admin, logs `create_room`
- `admin_update_room` (PATCH) — admin, logs `update_room`
- `admin_set_main_room` (POST) — admin, logs `set_main`
- `admin_reorder_rooms` (POST) — admin, logs `reorder`
- `admin_delete_room` (DELETE) — super, logs `delete_room`

**New endpoints:** `GET /admin/me`, `GET /admin/audit`, `GET /admin/admins`, `POST /admin/admins`, `DELETE /admin/admins/{email_hash}` — all as specified.

**Logout:** `/logout` already existed (`auth_logout`, deletes session + closes live sockets + clears cookie) — did nothing per branch instructions.

**Spec/reality mismatches found and resolved:**
1. `admin_strike_user` had no pre-existing `get_user`/not-found check (unlike `admin_ban`/`admin_mute_user`/`admin_delete_user`). Adding one as the spec's guard-placement pattern implies would have changed behavior — previously a nonexistent user silently returns `{"action": "none"}` via `process_strike`. I placed `_guard_target` before calling `process_strike` without adding a not-found check (it internally no-ops via `_protected_role` returning `None` for a missing user), preserving prior behavior. I also skip `log_admin_action` when `result["action"] == "none"` since no mutation occurred.
2. All named imports (`hash_email`, `get_user_by_token`) were already present as the spec anticipated — no duplicate imports added.

Not run/tested — per instructions, the orchestrator runs tests.
